Types of Variable

1. Based on the location of declaration.
	a. Local Variable / Temporary Variables
		-- Rule for Local Variables -> Initialize the local variables with their default values at lest because JVM will not provide the default vault to it
		-- Scope of local variable --> Local Variables are not accessible outside the block of its declaration
		
	b. Global Variable
		1. Static variable
		2. Non-static variable / Instance variable / data member
		
Scope of every Variable

2. Based on the type of value it holds
	a. Primitive Type variables
	b. Reference Type variables
	
Life Cycle of a variable

Declaration of a variable
Initialization of a variable
utilization of a variable